Class TestMethod

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class TestMethod
extends Object
implements org.jvnet.jaxb2_commons.lang.Equals, org.jvnet.jaxb2_commons.lang.HashCode, org.jvnet.jaxb2_commons.lang.ToString
    Information about a single test method. This will contain the name of the test method as attribute and a multiple Test Records within the test Method. Each TestRecord signifies a single execution of the given test method. Default input data can be supplied, they will be passed to every TestRecord as default values. Default may be overridden by specifying an entry of the same key in the actual TestRecord.

      • getTestRecord

        public List<TestRecord> getTestRecord()
        Gets the value of the testRecord property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the testRecord property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getTestRecord().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list TestRecord
